      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BEE MY LOVER (3) has come from wide barriers in the last two outings and is suited dropping back to maiden company having finished a close second in this grade two back at Newcastle. Race fit now and well served by this barrier so gets her chance to break through. NELLI TRISTAR (2) made a decent return after nearly seven months when he came from the back row for fourth last week at Newcastle. Fitter and draws well so  could pose a serious challenge. RUBATEEKI (1) will be fitter for recent racing and gets a much better draw so look for improvement. CORNELIUS (8) faces the starter for the first time. By Poster Boy and hails from the Anton Golino stable. Fifth in his latest trial at Menangle. Follow any market moves.",
